OL,3,CFinnish airline starts weighing
OL,4,Cpassengers before departure
OL,6,FThe weight of customers and their
OL,7,Fcarry-on luggage is typically
OL,8,Fcalculated using average weights
OL,9,Fsuggested by the Civil Aviation
OL,10,FAuthority and the European Aviation
OL,11,FSafety Authority, but airlines are
OL,12,Falso allowed to use their own data and
OL,13,Fmeasuring systems.
OL,15,FAirlines need to refresh their
OL,16,Fmeasurements every five years. Finnair
OL,17,Fhas been doing its own maths on
OL,18,Fpassenger and baggage weight averages
OL,19,Fsince 2018, so is due an update to the
OL,20,Ffigures.
